                            <comment id="275498" author="adilger" created="Wed, 15 Jul 2020 17:26:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Gian-Carlo, I&apos;m not aware of any reason that the order of these lines were changed, but I&apos;ve added James to the CC list here to get his feedback.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Feel free to submit a patch that reverts to the original order in &lt;tt&gt;autoMakefile.am&lt;/tt&gt; with a label:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;Fixes: 742897a967cf (&quot;LU-13274 uapi: make lnet UAPI headers C99 compliant&quot;)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;and add James and me as reviewers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;If this fixes your build issue and does not break any of the Jenkins builds, then there shouldn&apos;t be any problem to land it.  James is generally very responsive, so I&apos;m sure he&apos;ll comment if there was a good reason for the change.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="275496" author="jhammond" created="Wed, 15 Jul 2020 17:21:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Let&apos;s delete the snmp directory and see if anyone notices.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
